                            <p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Rāmanāthasvamin temple.</p>						                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Of the three unconnected pieces<note>The first two lines of pieces 1 and 2 are engraved in characters different from those of the other lines.</note> below, piece 1 refers to some exchange of land, and piece 2 contains a portion of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Pugaḻ śUḻnda</hi> etc., of the king.</p>						
                            
